  "prompt": "Why did Quora remove the 'needs improvement' tags?",
  "response": "On October 23, 2019, Quora announced the removal of the 'needs improvement' tag. The primary reason behind this decision was to enhance the user experience on the platform. Quora aimed to streamline its moderation process and make it easier for users to understand why their content might be flagged or not meet the platform's standards.\n\nPreviously, the 'needs improvement' tag was used to indicate that a piece of content did not meet Quora's quality guidelines. However, this often led to confusion and frustration among users, as it was sometimes unclear what specific adjustments were needed to meet the standards.\n\nBy removing this tag, Quora shifted towards clearer and more direct feedback methods, thereby helping users improve their contributions to the platform more effectively. The move was part of a broader effort to foster higher quality content and better interactions on Quora.",
